description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be the best Nurse you can be.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The nurses on the front line of Hampshire County Councils Adults Health and Care service do so much more than care, they transform lives. Our nurses are caregivers, advocates and true heroes of healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are currently offering opportunities for passionate and dedicated nurses to join the team at our brand-new facility, Clarence Unit at Woodcot Lodge. Located in the historic naval town of Gosport, Clarence Unit is a unique discharge service that supports hospital leavers either return home with a package of care, or on to a residential setting. This is an exciting opportunity to be part of a new and pioneering service that we are offering in partnership with local NHS providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can read more about this unique collaboration here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Surrounded by a well-resourced multi-disciplinary team, you will be fully supported in your determination to provide the highest quality care to our services users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE OFFER YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hampshire County Council cares for those who care and we recognise the outstanding contribution you make to people’s lives, so in return we offer a commitment to your development and wellbeing, enabling you to be the best nurse you can possibly be. &lt;br /&gt;This is offered alongside a competitive benefits package, including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• A £3,000 market supplement (pro-rata if part-time) in addition to your annual salary.&lt;br /&gt;• Access to Local Government Pension Scheme&lt;br /&gt;• A minimum 25 days annual leave entitlement&lt;br /&gt;• Family friendly policies&lt;br /&gt;• An exceptional, supportive team &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service users are at the heart of everything we do, and our sole aim is to give them the dignity, respect and independence that they deserve.&lt;/p&gt;
